 One end-of-the-year list that escaped our clutches until now was the Forbes  Ranking of Americas 100 Largest Banks, which included some notable local strength. 
 
Glacier Bancorp , parent to Bank of the San Juans , ranked high on the list, at number five. 
 
US Bancorp, or US Bank, was listed at number 58, and Wells Fargo ranked number 66, both respectable finishes on the list, which ranks banks based on metrics related to growth, profitability, capital adequacy and asset quality, Forbes said. 
 
All of the data Forbes relied on for the list is based on regulatory filings for the period ending Sept. 30, 2016. 
 
The magazines ranking of the 100 largest banks was borne out of the financial crisis of the late 2000s, when credit quality was cratering across the banking industry. 
 
 
 
